      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " مَنْ ضَرَبَ مَمْلُوكاً حَدّاً مِنَ الْحُدُودِ مِنْ غَيْرِ حَدٍّ أَوْجَبَهُ الْمَمْلُوكُ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ لَمْ يَكُنْ لِضَارِبِهِ كَفَّارَةٌ إِلَّا عِتْقُهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Hisham Bin Salim, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who whips an owned (slave), a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) from the Penalties, without a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) having been Obligated upon himself, there would not be an expiation except for his emancipation (libration)’."
        ]
      }
    }
